{
  "doc_id": "16213",
  "text": "For each sample, two 1.5 mm diameter samples of dried blood (equivalent to 3-5 µL of blood) [CITATION_1] were placed in the well of a 96-well PCR microplate (Axygen Scientific, Union City, CA). Each plate included two positive controls (P. vivax or P. falciparum) and three negative controls (two blood spots from a known malaria negative donor and one no-template reaction control). To remove haemoglobin, 70 µL of molecular biology grade water (Cellgro-Mediatech INC, Manassas, VA) were added to each well and the plate was incubated at 50 °C for five min, 21 °C for 15 s, 50 °C for 1.5 min, and 21 °C for 15 s. The water was then removed from each well and discarded.",
